							<h3 class="title aria-hidden">Post by Dragsbro on <abbr class="o-timestamp time" data-timestamp="1452549478000" title="Mon Jan 11 2016 22:57:58 GMT+0100 (Central European Standard Time)">Jan 11, 2016 at 10:57pm</abbr></h3>
							<div class="message"><font face="times new roman" size="3">First of all, <a rel="norewrite" href="http://irunaonline.boards.net/thread/2639/magic-ninja-guide" target="_blank">Reborner's guide</a>, even if a bit outdated now, is well made and full of truths o.o)/&nbsp;<br>Although, I'd want to make something more theoric, with detailed informations about skills and gameplays...and stuff &gt;.&gt;<br><br></font><div style="text-align:center;"><font face="times new roman"><u style="color:rgb(255, 0, 0);font-weight:bold;"><font size="6">About "Magic" ninja</font></u><br></font><div style="text-align:left;"><font face="times new roman" size="3"><br><div style="text-align:center;">What's the purpose of this? Well, being magic ninja at first meant to use the <b><u>magic</u></b> skills ninjas are given.&nbsp;</div><div style="text-align:center;">Nowadays, some people may refer to "magic" ninja as the "Silent Killing"-focused ones, which isn't really right because SK is <b><u>not</u></b>&nbsp;a magic skill, but isn't totally wrong either since a regular magic ninja using a Throwing weapon will have decent SK damages, and that still being a magic ninja after Lv300 is pretty rare (and not advised damages-wise, even with Phantom Flame highering magic, without the Lv340 skills)<br>Although, the Lv340 skills might separate these three or four type of ninjas more clearly: Physical focused, SK focused, Magic focused.<br>And of course, Hybrid ones. Which is (I think) the first purpose of Ninjas.</div></font></div></div><div class="spoiler_header"><a href="javascript:void(0);" onclick="$('#spoiler6905159').toggle();if ($('#spoiler6905159').is(':visible')) $(this).text('SPOILER: Click to hide');else $(this).text('SPOILER: Click to show');" style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span class="sptitle" style="cursor: pointer;" onclick="changespoil(this)"><div style="text-align:center;"><span style="font-size:10pt;"></span><font face="times new roman" color="#0029ff" size="7"><b><u>BUILDS</u></b></font><font style="font-size:10pt;" face="times new roman"><font size="7"></font></font></div></span></div><div class="spoiler" id="spoiler6905159" data-tag="spoiler"><font face="times new roman"><div style="text-align:center;"><font size="3">"&gt;"&nbsp;means "then"&nbsp;<br>"<b>/</b>"&nbsp;means the choice or order is up to you</font><u style="color:rgb(185, 25, 230);"><b><br><font size="5">Magic ninja builds (Throwing/Staff)</font></b></u></div></font><div align="center" style="text-align:left;"><font face="times new roman"><font color="ff0000" size="4"><br><u>INT&gt;DEX&gt;VIT </u>(for Struggler)<u>&gt;BL/GR,</u> then <u>CRT</u> or <u>VIT</u> or <u>AGI</u><br></font></font><span style="font-family:&quot;font-size:medium;"><font size="3">Probably the most effective of all the magic builds, as in the one giving the most MATK.</font></span><font face="times new roman"><font color="ff0000" size="4"><u><br></u></font></font></div><div align="center"><div style="text-align:left;"><font size="3" face="times new roman">Good survivability as well. Depending on your lvl and stat points, can also deal decent physical damages. <br>Although, if you don't care about it, you can drop the CRT for more VIT or EXP special stats.<br><table><tbody><tr><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><b>MATK</b></td><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><b><span><font color="#fafe09">★★★★★</font></span></b></td></tr><tr><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><b>ATK</b></td><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><b><font color="#fafe09">★★</font><br></b></td></tr><tr><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><b>Critical damages</b></td><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><font style="font-weight:bold;" color="#fafe09">★☆</font><br></td></tr><tr><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><b>Survivability</b></td><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><font color="#fafe09" style="font-weight:bold;">★★★☆</font></td></tr></tbody></table></font></div><font size="3" face="times new roman"><div style="text-align:left;"><br></div></font><div align="center"><font face="times new roman" size="3" color="ff0000"><b><u></u></b></font></div><div style="text-align:center;"><div style="text-align:left;"><span style="color:rgb(255, 0, 0);font-family:&quot;"><font size="4"><u>INT&gt;DEX&gt;AGI/VIT&gt;GL</u><br></font></span></div><font face="times new roman"><div style="text-align:left;"><font size="3">A build focused on both magic skills and evasion. The use of AGI can be associated with Magic Amp too, but this means less ATK (Staff vs Throw).<br>This build loses a bit of firepower but is <b>much</b> safer. High evasion is easily attainable as well as high HPs.<br><table><tbody><tr><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><b>MATK</b></td><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><font color="#fafe09">★★★★☆</font></td></tr><tr><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><b>ATK</b></td><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><font color="#fafe09">★☆</font></td></tr><tr><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><b>Critical damages</b></td><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><font color="#fafe09">★</font></td></tr><tr><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><b>Survivability</b></td><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><font color="#fafe09">★★★★★</font></td></tr></tbody></table><br></font></div><div style="text-align:left;"><br><div style="text-align:center;"><b><u><font size="5" color="#b919e6">Hybrid and SK ninja builds (Throwing)</font></u></b></div></div></font></div><div style="text-align:center;"><font face="times new roman"><div style="text-align:left;"><font size="4"><br></font></div><div style="text-align:left;"><br><font color="#ff0000" size="4"><u>INT&gt;CRT&gt;Minimum VIT for Struggler&gt;DEX,</u> then <u>GR/BL</u></font><br><font size="3">The use of VIT, additionally to Struggler's extra MATK, makes this build safer thanks to HP pool and Utsusemi. Build giving the most SK damages.</font><br><table><tbody><tr><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><b><font size="3">MATK</font></b></td><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><font size="3" color="#fafe09">★★★★</font></td></tr><tr><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><b><font size="3">ATK</font></b></td><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><font size="3" color="#fafe09">★☆</font></td></tr><tr><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><b><font size="3">Critical damages</font></b></td><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><font size="3" color="#fafe09">★★★★</font></td></tr><tr><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><b><font size="3">Survivability</font></b></td><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><font size="3"><font color="#fafe09">★★★</font><br></font></td></tr></tbody></table><div style="text-align:left;"><font size="4"><u style="color:rgb(255, 0, 0);"><br>INT&gt;DEX/CRT,</u><span style="color:rgb(255, 0, 0);"> then </span><span style="color:rgb(255, 0, 0);"><u>GR/BL</u>&nbsp;or </span><span style="color:rgb(255, 0, 0);"><u>STR</u></span></font><br><font size="3" color="#000000"> Provides ATK, MATK, Delay and crt damages. <br>You can get great damages with all of your skills, although none can be <i>totally</i> maxed out.<br>Adding STR or Line Boosts only depends on you, your equipments and gameplay.<br></font><table><tbody><tr><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><b><font size="3">MATK</font></b></td><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><font size="3" color="#fafe09">★★★</font></td></tr><tr><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><b><font size="3">ATK</font></b></td><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><font color="#fafe09" size="3">★★☆</font></td></tr><tr><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><b><font size="3">Critical damages</font></b></td><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><font size="3" color="#fafe09">★★★★☆</font></td></tr><tr><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><b><font size="3">Survivability</font></b></td><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><font size="3"><font color="#fafe09">★★</font><br></font></td></tr></tbody></table></div><br><font color="#ff0000" size="4"><u>INT&gt;CRT&gt;STR</u>, then <u>DEX</u> or <u>GR/RD/BL</u></font><br><font size="3">This build is focused on DoC but can also deal good damages with the other skills, thanks to Throwing weapons' versatile stats.</font></div><font size="3"><div style="text-align:left;">With right equipments and sets, SK damages won't get heavily affected (This means no Spin shield: CRT dmg down by STR.)<br>Delay equipments are needed.<table><tbody><tr><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><b><font size="3">MATK</font></b></td><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><font color="#fafe09">★☆</font></td></tr><tr><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><b><font size="3">ATK</font></b></td><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><font color="#fafe09">★★★☆</font></td></tr><tr><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><b><font size="3">Critical damages</font></b></td><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><font color="#fafe09">★★★★★</font></td></tr><tr><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><b><font size="3">Survivability</font></b></td><td style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:3px;"><font color="#fafe09">★★</font></td></tr></tbody></table></div></font></font></div></div></div><div class="spoiler_header"><a href="javascript:void(0);" onclick="$('#spoiler1475830').toggle();if ($('#spoiler1475830').is(':visible')) $(this).text('SPOILER: Click to hide');else $(this).text('SPOILER: Click to show');" style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span class="sptitle" style="cursor: pointer;" onclick="changespoil(this)"><div style="text-align:center;"><span style="font-size:10pt;"></span><font face="times new roman" color="#0029ff" size="7"><b><u>SKILLS</u></b></font><font face="times new roman" style="font-size:10pt;"><font size="3"></font></font></div></span></div><div class="spoiler" id="spoiler1475830" data-tag="spoiler"><font face="times new roman"><b style="font-size:medium;text-decoration:underline;"><font color="#ff0000"><br></font></b><font style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size:medium;">To become ninja, you need to complete a quest from Suigetsu at Minaula castle, available from Lv100+, collecting:<br>-20 Black Feather (Crow Samurai)<br>-20 Small shells (Kappa)<br>-20 Fan Feather (Tengu)<br>-20 Broken Flame Blower (Fire Cat)<br>Class Requirement: </font><font style="font-size:medium;"><font color="#4ae619">None. (You just can't be Ninja already or Samurai. Become another special class first to do the quest again.)</font><br></font><b style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size:medium;text-decoration:underline;"><br></b><font size="4" color="#ff0000"><b><u>Skills not out yet might be mispelled or/and misinterpreted.</u>&nbsp;<br><u>Click on "Quest:" to see skill quests requirements</u></b></font><br></font><b style="color:rgb(255, 0, 0);font-family:&quot;font-size:large;">Also, modifications on-going on Japanese version, see at the end of the section.</b><font face="times new roman"><font style="font-weight:bold;color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><br><u><br><font size="3">Shuriken Mastery:</font></u></font><font size="3"><br><font style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Passive skill boosting ATK and MATK when using a Throwing weapon.</font><br><font style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Level 1 - Ninja class change&nbsp;</font><br><font style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Level 2 - Item at Drafbourg:Immigrant Ward from Matif, Level 220 required</font><font><br><font color="#f209ee">More infos:</font><br><font style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">SLv1: ATK+50, MATK+100</font><br><font style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">SLv2: ATK+90, MATK+180 (※ +40 ATK, +80 MATK Compared to Lv1.)</font><b style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);text-decoration:underline;"><br></b><font><br><b style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><u>Kyuseijutsu Yang:</u></b><br><font color="#000000">Obtain the power of Yang. Enhance the effects of Tonjutsu and magic power. Possibility of creating 3 clones with Bunshin no Jutsu while the buff is active.</font><br>Level 1 - Item at Minaula city from Suigetsu&nbsp; or&nbsp; ninja class change (MP1)<br><font color="#f209ee">More infos:</font><br><font color="#000000">Effects:</font><br><font color="#000000">- Add [Yangton] effect and clones disappear.</font><br><font color="#000000">- If you have learned [Phantom Flame], [Phantom Flame] is renewed.</font><br><font color="#000000">- If [Yinton] is applied, it will be removed.</font><br><font color="#000000">- Triggers [Combo Stock] randomly during the effective time.</font><br><font color="#000000">- When using the skills designated by [Combo Stock], the damage of thoses skills AKA [Katon no Jutsu], [Suiton no Jutsu], [Raiton no Jutsu] and [Doton no Jutsu], increase.<br>- MaxMP + 500<br>- MATK + 20</font></font></font></font></font><font face="times new roman"><font size="3"><font><font><font color="#000000"><br><br></font><b><u>Kyuseijutsu Yin:</u></b><br>Obtain the power of Yin. Enhance the effects and resistance of clones.&nbsp;Possibility of creating 3 clones with Bunshin no Jutsu while the buff is active.<br>Level 1 - Item at Minaula city from Suigetsu  or  ninja class change (MP1)<br><font color="#f209ee">More infos:</font><br>Effects:<br>- Add [Yinton] effect and 3 clones.<br></font></font></font></font><font size="3"><span style="font-family:&quot;font-size:medium;">- If you have learned [Phantom Flame], [Phantom Flame] is renewed.<br></span><span style="font-family:&quot;font-size:medium;">- If [Yangton] is applied, it will be removed.<br>- MaxHP + 1000&nbsp;<br></span><font face="times new roman"><font><font>- Recover 1000 HP.<br>- Evasion +10%&nbsp;<br></font></font></font></font><font size="3" face="times new roman">- Allows Silent Killing to deal critical damages.</font><font size="3"><font face="times new roman"><font><font><br><br><b style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><u>Ni Rengeki:</u></b><br></font><font style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Passive skill allowing you to get a double atk from a normal hit. Doesn’t work if your weapon has an autoskill.</font><br><font style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Level 1 - Ninja class change&nbsp;<br></font><font style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Level 2 - Item at Minaula city from Sawa, Level 240 required</font><br><font style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><br><b style="text-decoration:underline;">Bunshin no Jutsu:</b></font><br><font style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Creates 3 clones to protect yourself. You can’t go over 3 clones with this skill, and you can only create 2 clones when paralyzed. Clones aren’t available when stunned or blinded. MP is required to keep clones while fighting.</font><br><font style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Level 1 -Ninja class change (MP128)</font><font><br><font color="#f209ee">More infos:</font><br></font><font style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">-Even at max DEX, <b>need -2 seconds</b><u> delay</u> from equipments to reduce it at minimum (1 second) <br>-Each clone drains 1% of MaxMP per second during battle. 3 clones = 3% per second.</font><br><b style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><u><br></u></b><b style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><u>Desperate Move:<br></u></b><font style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Heals your HP, heal amount being based on your Lv. If your current HP is less than 10% of your MaxHP, you get an additional heal and 3 clones are created. Cancel MP drain from clones and gives a MP regen buff.</font><br><font style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Level 1 - Ninja class change (MP24)</font><br><font color="#f209ee">More infos:</font><br>-At 200(?) DEX, skill delay maxed (1 second) <br>-MP heal buff is fixed at 1% MaxMP per second for 10 seconds.<br><br><b style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><u><font>Dance of C</font>lo<font>nes:</font></u></b><br><font style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Physical attack skill. The damages and delay are based on your critical damages and your clones amount: each clone deals damages and adds 1 second delay. Unavailable if stunned or blind.</font><br><font style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Level 1 - Quest at Minaula city from Suigetsu, Level 140 required (MP48)</font><br><font style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Level 2 - Quest at Minaula city from Suishin, Level 280 required (MP72)</font><font><br><div class="spoiler_header"><a href="javascript:void(0);" onclick="$('#spoiler9883619').toggle();if ($('#spoiler9883619').is(':visible')) $(this).text('SPOILER: Click to hide');else $(this).text('SPOILER: Click to show');" style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span class="sptitle" style="cursor: pointer;" onclick="changespoil(this)"><font color="#f209ee">Quest:</font></span></div><div class="spoiler" id="spoiler9883619" data-tag="spoiler"><font color="#000000">For SLv1:<br>- Ganei ×1 <br>- Ippon-datara&nbsp;×25 <br>- Ittan-momen ×50 <br>- Fire cat ×75<br><br>For SLv2:<br>- Gauchel ×1<br>- Giga<span>ntes</span> ×50 <br>- Jacbos ×50 <br>- Werewolf fur ×5 </font><font color="#f209ee">.</font></div><font color="#f209ee">More infos:</font><br></font><font style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">According to <span itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Person"><a href="/user/9666" class="user-link js-user-link user-9666 group-0" itemprop="url" title="@grindelwald"><span itemprop="name">NightBreeze</span></a></span>                  ,<br>-DoC lv1:<br>3 clones - 11.4 * auto atk dmg<br>2 clones - 7.6 * auto atk dmg<br>1 clone - 3.8 * auto atk dmg<br><br>-DoC lv2:<br>3 clones - 12.3 * auto atk dmg<br>2 clones - 8.2 * auto atk dmg<br>1 clone - 4.1 * auto atk dmg</font><font style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><br><br><